Package gw.api.domain

Interface PublicGroupParentViewFinder

public interface PublicGroupParentViewFinder
Provides methods for finding the parent group of a single group or for all groups in an organization.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type
    Method
    Description
    IQueryBeanResult
    findAll()
    Find the parents for all groups, regardless of organization.
    IQueryBeanResult<GroupParentView>
    findAllInOrganization(Key organizationId)
    Find the parents for all groups in the given organization, or for all groups that have no organization set if the given organization is null.
    Key
    findParent(Key groupId)
    Find the id of the parent group for the given group

  • Method Details

    • findAllInOrganization

      IQueryBeanResult<GroupParentView> findAllInOrganization(Key organizationId)
      Find the parents for all groups in the given organization, or for all groups that have no organization set if the given organization is null. The query processor will return a series of GroupParentView entities specifying a group id and a parent id. All entities will have a non null group id. The GroupParentView for the root group will have a null parent id, all other entities returned will have a non null parent id.
      Parameters:
      organizationId - the id of the organization or null
      Returns:
      a query processor that will return GroupParentView for all groups in the given organization or all groups with no organization if organizationId is null.

    • findAll

      IQueryBeanResult findAll()
      Find the parents for all groups, regardless of organization. The query processor will return a series of GroupParentView entities specifying a group id and a parent id. All entities will have a non null group id. The GroupParentView for a root group will have a null parent id, all other entities returned will have a non null parent id.
      Returns:
      a query processor that will return GroupParentView for all groups

    • findParent

      Key findParent(Key groupId)
      Find the id of the parent group for the given group
      Parameters:
      groupId - the id of the group, must not be null
      Returns:
      the id of the group's parent, or null if it is a root group
